HEADWORD: Conchoid
<hw>Con"choid</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr. <?/; <?/ shell
+ <grk>e'i^dos</grk> form: cf. F. <ets>concho⟦ium⟧de</ets>.]</ety>
<fld>(Geom.)</fld> <def>A curve, of the fourth degree, first made use of
by the Greek geometer, Nicomedes, who invented it for the purpose of
trisecting an angle and duplicating the cube.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Conchoidal</ent>⟦br⟧
